OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA band of wet and rather windy
OL,6,Fweather will feed eastwards across the
OL,7,Fregion this morning. Much sunnier
OL,8,Fskies will follow for the afternoon,
OL,9,Fwith isolated showers developing
OL,10,Flater, and the brisk winds will ease a
OL,11,Flittle too.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FThe evening will start
OL,14,Flargely fine with some late sunshine.
OL,15,FHowever, more in the way of cloud is
OL,16,Flikely to develop overnight bringing a
OL,17,Ffew showers. Staying breezy, but frost-
OL,18,Ffree.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
